properties.areaDesc: Northern Inland Waters Including The San Juan Islands
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 23 at 8:36PM PST until January 24 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, southeast winds 25 to 35 kt. For
the Small Craft Advisory, south winds 15 to 25 kt.

* WHERE...Northern Inland Waters Including The San Juan Islands.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until midnight PST tonight. For
the Small Craft Advisory, from midnight tonight to 4 PM PST
Friday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
A Gale Warning means winds of 34 to 47 knots are imminent or
occurring. Operating a vessel in gale conditions requires
experience and properly equipped vessels. It is highly
recommended that mariners without the proper experience seek safe
harbor prior to the onset of gale conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT PST TONIGHT... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 4 PM PST FRIDAY
